result.formatted_address: 63 Nathan Rd, Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong
result.name: Pho Hoi An

reviews.text: Rarely do I get decent vietnamese food in Hong Kong,  this one was a pleasant surprise for me. Good service and food were decent and tasted good.

Food was ok, service terrible.  We were still seated and chatting and they took away everything, even my tea cup, which they charged me for, by the way.  Absolute worst service of any viet restaurant I have been to in HK.

I don't understand the bad reviews. I came here for lunch, despite the negative feedback and it was perfectly fine. The food was good and came fast, the waitresses were kind, I honestly don't see what the issue is.  🤷‍♂
I’ve had better Vietnamese food than this place. The lime soda doesn’t taste fresh and the pork chop vermicelli is average. The meal was a decent price and it wasn’t bad food.
its fine for a quick healthy inexpensive bite.

result.name: iSQUARE

reviews.text: Isquare  Is a nice shopping mall it has really call art work in front of it. It's really busy has a lot of nice shops that are all open past 10:00 p.m. It's in a convenient location from the Subway. Has some good restaurants in it. And the movie theater

It's a modern and great design shopping center and close to my hotel. I went here for a lunch and found Mark & Spencer on the ground floor and shopped a bit here. Overall, it's a nice shopping center.
Good for shopping (M&S clothing and food hall, marketplace), kids-r-us and other kid brands, very good cinema, linked to TST MTR train station
Visited the EyeLounge.  Very nice location with breath taking views of the city! Good drinks and very nice restaurant and cuisine.
High end shopping mall in Kowloon. Big brands.
